'''Kunioshitomi no Kami''' (国忍富神, クニオシトミ) is a deity in {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話|12=draft}}.

== Overview ==
Kunioshitomi no Kami is mentioned in the ''{{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}}'' as a grandchild of {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|12=draft}}, but no details about the deity are provided beyond the name. The deity is one of the {{ill|The 17 Generations of Deities|ja|十七世神|12=draft}}, classified as a {{ill|Kunitsukami|ja|国津神|12=draft}}.

The name can be broken down into "Kuni" (land), "Oshi" (dominating or imposing), and "Tomi" (abundance), collectively interpreted as "the land is overwhelmingly abundant." The deity's role as an agricultural god is believed to reflect the prosperity inherited from {{ill|Hinaterinukatabichioikochini no Kami|ja|日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神|1=Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|12=draft}}, who symbolizes fertile fields.{{Sfn|Nishinomiya|2014|p=382}}

The genealogy of the {{ill|Susa Shrine|ja|須佐神社|12=draft}}'s priestly Susa clan also mentions Kunioshitomi no Kami as a descendant of {{ill|Kayanarumi no Kami|ja|カヤナルミ|12=draft}}, an offspring of Ōkuninushi.

== Genealogy ==
[[File:Ohokuninushi family tree.png|right|thumb|250px|Genealogy of Ōkuninushi (as per the ''Kojiki''). Blue represents male deities, red represents female deities, and yellow represents deities of unknown gender.]]

* '''Torinarumi-no-Kami Lineage'''  
{{Unbulleted list|Kunioshitomi no Kami was born to {{ill|Torinarumi-no-Kami|ja|鳥鳴海神|1=Torinarumi-no-Kami|1=Torinarumi-no-Kami|12=draft}} and {{ill|Hinaterinukatabichioikochini no Kami|ja|日名照額田毘道男伊許知邇神|1=Hinateri-Nukada-Bichio-Ikochini-no-Kami|12=draft}}. Kunioshitomi no Kami married {{ill|Ashinadaka no Kami|ja|葦那陀迦神|1=Ashinataka-no-Kami|12=draft}} and had a child, {{ill|Hayamikanotakesahayajinumi no Kami|ja|速甕之多気佐波夜遅奴美神|1=Hayamike-no-Takekasayanosunumi-no-Kami|12=draft}}.}}

* '''Kayanarumi Lineage'''  
{{Unbulleted list|In the genealogical records of Susa Shrine, Kunioshitomi no Kami is listed as a descendant of {{ill|Kayanarumi no Kami|ja|カヤナルミ|12=draft}}, an offspring of Ōkuninushi. The deity is also noted as the ancestor of the Susa clan, with a child named Kumoyama no Kami, though the consort and mother are not specified.}}

== Shrines Dedicated ==
* '''Tomi Shrine''' ({{ill|Hikawa Town|ja|斐川町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Izumo City|ja|出雲市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Shimane Prefecture|ja|島根県|12=draft}})

